{"author":{"id":"622048132944212c32e1b63ec36e2ca816992dfb4432ea3388f2f08fbab7090f"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1763626646,"nonce":"ZqmS5tlKEaEt7DpWmU4bcrl0usw=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOAW4Y0s7T--Bd","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/7438#issuecomment-3556499549"},"message":"https://github.com/mbhall88/nohuman could be interesting for Human reads:\n\n\u003e During recent benchmarking, I found Kraken was detecting many more human reads than the nohuman database. It turns out Kraken masks low-complexity regions by default when building its DB and I had left this on when building the nohuman database.\n\u003e Fix: I rebuilt everything without masking, and the difference is dramatic. I also took the opportunity to make a new database from the second release from the Human Pangenome Consortium (HPRC.r2)\n| Pipeline / Database Used        | Human reads detected |\n|---------------------------------|----------------------|\n| Kraken (standard DB)            |  113,756           |\n| nohuman (HPRC.r1 — masked)      |  2,624             |\n| nohuman (HPRC.r1 — unmasked)    |  218,808           |\n| nohuman (HPRC.r2 — unmasked)    |  225,944           |\nnohuman now includes support for selecting specific datasets\nThe unmasked HPRC.r2 database is now the default\nStrongly recommend existing users update + redownload the DB\nRepo: https://github.com/mbhall88/nohuman","files":null}]}